# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EcoTrace — Environment Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in the values from your Firebase /
# Google Cloud projects. Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_
# to the client bundle. Because this is a serverless, client-side app, the
# Gemini key is protected by Google Cloud API key restrictions (service
# scope + HTTP referrers) — see DEPLOYMENT.md for the hardening checklist.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Firebase project config (Project settings → General → Your apps) ---
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=YOUR_FIREBASE_API_KEY
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=000000000000
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:000000000000:web:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Optional — enables Google Analytics 4 in production builds only.
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# --- Gemini API key (Google AI Studio) ---
# Restricted in Google Cloud Console to the Generative Language API only,
# and to your Firebase Hosting HTTP referrers.
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY
